Although we have derived the spectral density in eq 36 by using our single exponential approximation to CK?) (eq 24), we shall now show that this expression for the spectral density, and hence eq 37 and 38 for the relaxation times and the NOE, are actually exact when (1) the overall motion is isotropic, (2) internal motions are much faster than the overall motion and lie in the extreme
narrowing limit, and (3) , is defined as the area of the correlation function (eq 26). This is an important result. It explains why our model-free approach to analyzing relaxation data works so well in many cases of interest.
