the extreme narrowing limit) and the fact that the exact values of the order parameters are very small. As we shall see below, 7, and NOE data at 68 MHz determine P2 and re better when P2 is larger (i.e., P2 > 0.01) and/or tc is faster.
We now present the results of a systematic investigation of the range of validity of the model-free approach. The conclusions reached by exploring a large number of simulated data will be illustrated with numerous examples.
We consider first the case where the internal motions are in
the extreme narrowing limit. In this limit, the spectral density
is given exactly by eq 36; i.e., one has exactly

