termining the relaxation parameters, e.g., o>c + for 13C dipolar relaxation. We found that for fast internal motions, virtually exact values of P2 and tc can be obtained from a pair of relaxation parameters (e.g., NOE and 7,) at two fields. For example, for a 13C NMR frequency of ~90 MHz, if ~ 10 ns, motions such that tc 5 100 ps may be considered fast. At a given magnetic field and fixed tm, as tc decreases the agreement between the two sides of eq 61 gets better and, of course, if tc is fast enough, eq 61 becomes an identity. For example, for 13C-H dipolar relaxation at a Larmor frequency of 90.5 MHz, if = 10 ns and tc = 25

