motions for carbons & and e are not far from the extreme narrowing limit. The «f2’s and re’s obtained from TVs at both fields by using eq 59a and 59b, respectively, are better than the values obtained
analytically from , and NOE at high field, but not as accurate as the results from , and NOE at low field. It is remarkable
how good the general agreement between the values is, considering
the simplicity of the analysis of this system where the motion is highly anisotropic. Of course the agreement between exact and calculated values would be even better for internal motions on a faster time scale. In summary, the trend in the accuracy of the extracted j12 and re seems to be basically unaltered by the form of the correlation function for overall motion. The accuracy of j12 and re depends essentially only on the magnitude of the order parameter and the time scale of internal motions. Even in the anisotropic case, for fast internal motions accurate values of S’2 and re can be extracted by using a straightforward fitting procedure or, for motions close to the extreme narrowing limit, from simple analytical formulas.
